
## üß™ REST API Endpoints

> üîó **Base URL:** `http://localhost:5000`

---

### üì¶ Product APIs (`/product`)

| Method | Endpoint       | Description                     | Body Params               | Auth    |
| ------ | -------------- | ------------------------------- | ------------------------- | ------- |
| GET    | `/product`     | Get all products                | ‚Äì                         | ‚ùå       |
| GET    | `/product/:id` | Get product by ID               | ‚Äì                         | ‚ùå       |
| POST   | `/product`     | Add a new product with image(s) | ‚úÖ `form-data` (see below) | ‚úÖ Admin |
| PUT    | `/product/:id` | Update a product by ID          | ‚úÖ `form-data` (see below) | ‚úÖ Admin |
| DELETE | `/product/:id` | Delete a product by ID          | ‚Äì                         | ‚úÖ Admin |

#### üì§ POST/PUT `/product` (with images)

Use `multipart/form-data` with the following fields:

| Field    | Type     | Description                          |
| -------- | -------- | ------------------------------------ |
| id       | Number   | Product ID                           |
| name     | String   | Product name                         |
| sku      | String   | SKU                                  |
| desc     | String   | Description                          |
| price    | Number   | Price                                |
| discount | String   | Discount                             |
| material | String   | Material (e.g., "14K Gold")          |
| stock    | Boolean  | In stock or not                      |
| rating   | Number   | Rating (e.g., 4.5)                   |
| reviews  | Number   | Number of reviews                    |
| category | ObjectId | Category ID (MongoDB ID)             |
| **img**  | File(s)  | Upload multiple image files (max: 5) |

‚úÖ Images are saved in `/upload`, with URLs like:
`http://localhost:5000/upload/<filename>`

---

### üóÇÔ∏è Category APIs (`/category`)

| Method | Endpoint        | Description        | Body Params |
| ------ | --------------- | ------------------ | ----------- |
| GET    | `/category`     | Get all categories | ‚Äì           |
| GET    | `/category/:id` | Get category by ID | ‚Äì           |
| POST   | `/category`     | Add a new category | ‚úÖ JSON      |
| PUT    | `/category/:id` | Update a category  | ‚úÖ JSON      |
| DELETE | `/category/:id` | Delete a category  | ‚Äì           |

#### üì§ POST / PUT body example (JSON):

```json
{
  "name": "Rings",
  "description": "All ring collections"
}
```

---

### üõí Order APIs (`/order`)

| Method | Endpoint            | Description         | Body Params        | Auth    |
| ------ | ------------------- | ------------------- | ------------------ | ------- |
| POST   | `/order/place`      | Place a new order   | ‚úÖ JSON (see below) | ‚ùå       |
| GET    | `/order`            | Get all orders      | ‚Äì                  | ‚úÖ Admin |
| GET    | `/order/:id`        | Get order by ID     | ‚Äì                  | ‚úÖ Admin |
| PUT    | `/order/status/:id` | Update order status | ‚úÖ JSON `{status}`  | ‚úÖ Admin |

#### üì§ POST `/order/place` Body Example:

```json
{
  "user": {
    "userId": "12345",
    "name": "John Doe",
    "email": "john@example.com",
    "phone": "1234567890",
    "address": {
      "street": "123 Main St",
      "city": "New York",
      "state": "NY",
      "postalCode": "10001",
      "country": "USA"
    }
  },
  "items": [
    {
      "product": "608d1f8b2f799a0015a43c2d",
      "quantity": 2,
      "priceAtPurchase": 50,
      "discountedPrice": 45
    },
    {
      "product": "608d1f8b2f799a0015a43c2e",
      "quantity": 1,
      "priceAtPurchase": 60,
      "discountedPrice": 55
    }
  ],
  "totalAmount": 150.00,
  "deliveryFee": 10.00,
  "gstAmount": 8.00,
  "grandTotal": 168.00
}
```

#### ‚úÖ PUT `/order/status/:id` Body Example:

```json
{
  "status": "shipped"
}
```

> Allowed `status` values: `"pending"`, `"confirmed"`, `"shipped"`, `"delivered"`, `"cancelled"`

